{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775839936684,"sessionID":"ses_287b1c100ffemr0gD7SezJNHgY","part":{"id":"prt_d784f00aa001EDvEO4tAk3QzLW","messageID":"msg_d784ef42e001cWCh75MDykCQyh","sessionID":"ses_287b1c100ffemr0gD7SezJNHgY","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775839962693,"sessionID":"ses_287b1c100ffemr0gD7SezJNHgY","part":{"id":"prt_d784f0647001oOUubGoWoT2XKs","messageID":"msg_d784ef42e001cWCh75MDykCQyh","sessionID":"ses_287b1c100ffemr0gD7SezJNHgY","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_7708e02361e44697abeed0cc","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# Proposal: AR-002 — CRD CodeInterpreter 类型定义\n\n## Summary\n\nDefine Kubernetes Custom Resource Definition (CRD) types for `CodeInterpreter` in the `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1` module. This type enables the AgentCube control plane to manage code execution environment specifications programmatically.\n\n## Purpose\n\n`CodeInterpreter` CRD provides a declarative way to configure code execution environments for AI agents:\n\n- **Container orchestration**: Define container images, resources, environment variables\n- **Session management**: Configure max session duration, idle timeout\n- **Authentication**: Support for authentication modes (picod, none)\n- **Warm pool**: Pre-warmed pod scaling for faster cold start\n\nThis CRD is consumed by:\n- Workload Manager (creates/updates CodeInterpreter resources)\n- client-go library (generated, provides typed clients, listers, informers)\n- Helm chart CRDs (generated from these types via controller-gen)\n\n## Scope\n\n### Deliverables\n\n| Deliverable | Path | Description |\n|-------------|------|-------------|\n| Go types | `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/types.go` | CodeInterpreter type definitions |\n| Register | `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/register.go` | Scheme registration |\n| Doc | `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/doc.go` | Package documentation |\n| zz_generated.deepcopy.go | `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/zz_generated.deepcopy.go` | DeepCopy methods |\n\n### API Surface\n\n```\nGroup:   runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\nVersion: v1alpha1\nResource: codeinterpreters (Namespaced)\n```\n\n### CodeInterpreter Spec Fields\n\n| Field | Type | Required | Default | Description |\n|-------|------|----------|---------|-------------|\n| `authMode` | `AuthMode` (enum) | No | `\"picod\"` | Authentication mode: `picod`, `none` |\n| `maxSessionDuration` | `string` | No | `\"8h\"` | Maximum session lifetime |\n| `sessionTimeout` | `string` | No | `\"15m\"` | Idle timeout before cleanup |\n| `ports` | `[]TargetPort` | No | - | Port configuration array |\n| `template` | `ContainerTemplateSpec` | Yes | - | Container specification |\n| `warmPoolSize` | `int32` | No | `0` | Pre-warmed pod count |\n\n### Shared Types\n\n- **TargetPort**: `port` (int32, required), `protocol` (HTTP/HTTPS), `name` (string), `pathPrefix` (string)\n- **ContainerTemplateSpec**: `image`, `command`, `args`, `env`, `resources`, `runtimeClassName`\n- **AuthMode**: Enum with values `picod` and `none`\n\n### Status Subresource\n\nCodeInterpreter includes a `status` subresource with:\n- `conditions` ([]metav1.Condition)\n- `observedGeneration` (int64)\n- `ready` (bool)\n\n## Impact Analysis\n\n### Dependencies\n\n| Dependency | Version | Role |\n|------------|---------|------|\n| `k8s.io/api/core/v1` | ^1.32 | Container, EnvVar, ResourceRequirements |\n| `k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1` | ^1.32 | ObjectMeta, TypeMeta, conditions |\n| `k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime` | ^1.32 | Scheme, runtime.Object |\n| `sigs.k8s.io/controller-tools/pkg/runtime` | ^0.17.2 | controller-gen markers |\n| `sigs.k8s.io/controller-tools/pkg/crd` | ^0.17.2 | CRD generation |\n\n### Downstream Consumers\n\n1. **client-go** — Generated Kubernetes client code depends on these types\n2. **Helm CRDs** — `make gen-crd` generates YAML from these types to `manifests/charts/base/crds/`\n3. **Controllers** — Workload Manager reads/writes these CRs\n\n### Risks\n\n| Risk | Severity | Mitigation |\n|------|----------|------------|\n| Type mismatch with client-go | High | Ensure type names match client-go expectations (CodeInterpreter) |\n| CRD validation gaps | Medium | Add kubebuilder markers for OpenAPI schema validation |\n| Breaking API changes | Medium | Version as v1alpha1; reserve v1 for future stable release |\n\n## Alternatives Considered\n\n### Alternative 1: Use embedded corev1.Container directly\n\n**Approach**: Embed `corev1.Container` directly in CRD spec.\n\n**Pros**: \n- Full Container validation out of the box\n- No custom type needed\n\n**Cons**:\n- Exposes K8s internals that may not be relevant\n- Makes CRD schema overly complex\n- Unnecessary fields for code interpreter use case\n\n**Decision**: Use custom `ContainerTemplateSpec` with selective fields.\n\n### Alternative 2: Combine with AgentRuntime\n\n**Approach**: Single CRD with `runtimeType` field.\n\n**Pros**:\n- Single CRD to manage\n\n**Cons**:\n- Violates K8s CRD conventions\n- Makes RBAC and controller logic more complex\n- Loses type safety\n\n**Decision**: Keep separate CRDs per K8s best practices.\n\n### Alternative 3: Use external CRD definitions without Go types\n\n**Approach**: Define CRDs manually in YAML without Go types.\n\n**Pros**:\n- Faster initial setup\n\n**Cons**:\n- No type safety\n- No client-go generation\n- Manual synchronization needed\n- No DeepCopy methods\n\n**Decision**: Use Go types + controller-gen for type safety and automated CRD generation.\n\n## Implementation Plan\n\n1. Define `CodeInterpreter`, `CodeInterpreterList`, `CodeInterpreterSpec`, `CodeInterpreterStatus` in `types.go`\n2. Add kubebuilder markers for CRD generation\n3. Register types in `register.go`\n4. Run `make generate` to produce deepcopy functions\n5. Verify with `make gen-crd` and check CRD YAML output\n6. Verify with `make gen-client` ensures client-go compatibility\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] CodeInterpreter CRD can be created via kubectl\n- [ ] `make gen-crd` produces valid CRD YAML in `manifests/charts/base/crds/`\n- [ ] `make gen-client` succeeds without type errors\n- [ ] Go types compile without errors (`go build ./pkg/apis/...`)","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/proposal.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.\n\nLSP errors detected in other files:\n<diagnostics file=\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/types_test.go\">\nERROR [27:11] cannot use PodSpec{…} (value of struct type PodSpec) as *PodSpec value in struct literal\nERROR [108:5] unknown field WarmPoolSize in struct literal of type ContainerTemplateSpec\nERROR [226:29] undefined: original\nERROR [289:26] undefined: original\nERROR [465:10] undefined: ResourceRequirements\nERROR [473:12] spec.NewQuantity undefined (type *ContainerSpec has no field or method NewQuantity)\n</diagnostics>","metadata":{"diagnostics":{"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/types.go":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/types_test.go":[{"range":{"start":{"line":26,"character":10},"end":{"line":30,"character":5}},"severity":1,"code":"IncompatibleAssign","codeDescription":{"href":"https://pkg.go.dev/golang.org/x/tools/internal/typesinternal#IncompatibleAssign"},"source":"compiler","message":"cannot use PodSpec{…} (value of struct type PodSpec) as *PodSpec value in struct literal"},{"range":{"start":{"line":107,"character":4},"end":{"line":107,"character":16}},"severity":1,"code":"MissingLitField","codeDescription":{"href":"https://pkg.go.dev/golang.org/x/tools/internal/typesinternal#MissingLitField"},"source":"compiler","message":"unknown field WarmPoolSize in struct literal of type ContainerTemplateSpec"},{"range":{"start":{"line":225,"character":28},"end":{"line":225,"character":36}},"severity":1,"code":"UndeclaredName","codeDescription":{"href":"https://pkg.go.dev/golang.org/x/tools/internal/typesinternal#UndeclaredName"},"source":"compiler","message":"undefined: original"},{"range":{"start":{"line":288,"character":25},"end":{"line":288,"character":33}},"severity":1,"code":"UndeclaredName","codeDescription":{"href":"https://pkg.go.dev/golang.org/x/tools/internal/typesinternal#UndeclaredName"},"source":"compiler","message":"undefined: original"},{"range":{"start":{"line":464,"character":9},"end":{"line":464,"character":29}},"severity":1,"code":"UndeclaredName","codeDescription":{"href":"https://pkg.go.dev/golang.org/x/tools/internal/typesinternal#UndeclaredName"},"source":"compiler","message":"undefined: ResourceRequirements"},{"range":{"start":{"line":472,"character":11},"end":{"line":472,"character":22}},"severity":1,"code":"MissingFieldOrMethod","codeDescription":{"href":"https://pkg.go.dev/golang.org/x/tools/internal/typesinternal#MissingFieldOrMethod"},"source":"compiler","message":"spec.NewQuantity undefined (type *ContainerSpec has no field or method NewQuantity)"}],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/register.go":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/doc.go":[]},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/proposal.md","exists":true,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775839962668,"end":1775839962689}}}}
