{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775839967574,"sessionID":"ses_287b1c100ffemr0gD7SezJNHgY","part":{"id":"prt_d784f76be001K1T8Uyttbx2vFb","messageID":"msg_d784f6674001mEly6KxQnnQjvC","sessionID":"ses_287b1c100ffemr0gD7SezJNHgY","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_ed2ce980141e4456a3359c5d","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/proposal.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Proposal: AR-002 — CRD CodeInterpreter 类型定义\n2: \n3: ## Summary\n4: \n5: Define Kubernetes Custom Resource Definition (CRD) types for `CodeInterpreter` in the `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1` module. This type enables the AgentCube control plane to manage code execution environment specifications programmatically.\n6: \n7: ## Purpose\n8: \n9: `CodeInterpreter` CRD provides a declarative way to configure code execution environments for AI agents:\n10: \n11: - **Container orchestration**: Define container images, resources, environment variables\n12: - **Session management**: Configure max session duration, idle timeout\n13: - **Authentication**: Support for authentication modes (picod, none)\n14: - **Warm pool**: Pre-warmed pod scaling for faster cold start\n15: \n16: This CRD is consumed by:\n17: - Workload Manager (creates/updates CodeInterpreter resources)\n18: - client-go library (generated, provides typed clients, listers, informers)\n19: - Helm chart CRDs (generated from these types via controller-gen)\n20: \n21: ## Scope\n22: \n23: ### Deliverables\n24: \n25: | Deliverable | Path | Description |\n26: |-------------|------|-------------|\n27: | Go types | `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/types.go` | CodeInterpreter type definitions |\n28: | Register | `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/register.go` | Scheme registration |\n29: | Doc | `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/doc.go` | Package documentation |\n30: | zz_generated.deepcopy.go | `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/zz_generated.deepcopy.go` | DeepCopy methods |\n31: \n32: ### API Surface\n33: \n34: ```\n35: Group:   runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\n36: Version: v1alpha1\n37: Resource: codeinterpreters (Namespaced)\n38: ```\n39: \n40: ### CodeInterpreter Spec Fields\n41: \n42: | Field | Type | Required | Default | Description |\n43: |-------|------|----------|---------|-------------|\n44: | `authMode` | `AuthMode` (enum) | No | `\"picod\"` | Authentication mode: `picod`, `none` |\n45: | `maxSessionDuration` | `string` | No | `\"8h\"` | Maximum session lifetime |\n46: | `sessionTimeout` | `string` | No | `\"15m\"` | Idle timeout before cleanup |\n47: | `ports` | `[]TargetPort` | No | - | Port configuration array |\n48: | `template` | `ContainerTemplateSpec` | Yes | - | Container specification |\n49: | `warmPoolSize` | `int32` | No | `0` | Pre-warmed pod count |\n50: \n51: ### Shared Types\n52: \n53: - **TargetPort**: `port` (int32, required), `protocol` (HTTP/HTTPS), `name` (string), `pathPrefix` (string)\n54: - **ContainerTemplateSpec**: `image`, `command`, `args`, `env`, `resources`, `runtimeClassName`\n55: - **AuthMode**: Enum with values `picod` and `none`\n56: \n57: ### Status Subresource\n58: \n59: CodeInterpreter includes a `status` subresource with:\n60: - `conditions` ([]metav1.Condition)\n61: - `observedGeneration` (int64)\n62: - `ready` (bool)\n63: \n64: ## Impact Analysis\n65: \n66: ### Dependencies\n67: \n68: | Dependency | Version | Role |\n69: |------------|---------|------|\n70: | `k8s.io/api/core/v1` | ^1.32 | Container, EnvVar, ResourceRequirements |\n71: | `k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1` | ^1.32 | ObjectMeta, TypeMeta, conditions |\n72: | `k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime` | ^1.32 | Scheme, runtime.Object |\n73: | `sigs.k8s.io/controller-tools/pkg/runtime` | ^0.17.2 | controller-gen markers |\n74: | `sigs.k8s.io/controller-tools/pkg/crd` | ^0.17.2 | CRD generation |\n75: \n76: ### Downstream Consumers\n77: \n78: 1. **client-go** — Generated Kubernetes client code depends on these types\n79: 2. **Helm CRDs** — `make gen-crd` generates YAML from these types to `manifests/charts/base/crds/`\n80: 3. **Controllers** — Workload Manager reads/writes these CRs\n81: \n82: ### Risks\n83: \n84: | Risk | Severity | Mitigation |\n85: |------|----------|------------|\n86: | Type mismatch with client-go | High | Ensure type names match client-go expectations (CodeInterpreter) |\n87: | CRD validation gaps | Medium | Add kubebuilder markers for OpenAPI schema validation |\n88: | Breaking API changes | Medium | Version as v1alpha1; reserve v1 for future stable release |\n89: \n90: ## Alternatives Considered\n91: \n92: ### Alternative 1: Use embedded corev1.Container directly\n93: \n94: **Approach**: Embed `corev1.Container` directly in CRD spec.\n95: \n96: **Pros**: \n97: - Full Container validation out of the box\n98: - No custom type needed\n99: \n100: **Cons**:\n101: - Exposes K8s internals that may not be relevant\n102: - Makes CRD schema overly complex\n103: - Unnecessary fields for code interpreter use case\n104: \n105: **Decision**: Use custom `ContainerTemplateSpec` with selective fields.\n106: \n107: ### Alternative 2: Combine with AgentRuntime\n108: \n109: **Approach**: Single CRD with `runtimeType` field.\n110: \n111: **Pros**:\n112: - Single CRD to manage\n113: \n114: **Cons**:\n115: - Violates K8s CRD conventions\n116: - Makes RBAC and controller logic more complex\n117: - Loses type safety\n118: \n119: **Decision**: Keep separate CRDs per K8s best practices.\n120: \n121: ### Alternative 3: Use external CRD definitions without Go types\n122: \n123: **Approach**: Define CRDs manually in YAML without Go types.\n124: \n125: **Pros**:\n126: - Faster initial setup\n127: \n128: **Cons**:\n129: - No type safety\n130: - No client-go generation\n131: - Manual synchronization needed\n132: - No DeepCopy methods\n133: \n134: **Decision**: Use Go types + controller-gen for type safety and automated CRD generation.\n135: \n136: ## Implementation Plan\n137: \n138: 1. Define `CodeInterpreter`, `CodeInterpreterList`, `CodeInterpreterSpec`, `CodeInterpreterStatus` in `types.go`\n139: 2. Add kubebuilder markers for CRD generation\n140: 3. Register types in `register.go`\n141: 4. Run `make generate` to produce deepcopy functions\n142: 5. Verify with `make gen-crd` and check CRD YAML output\n143: 6. Verify with `make gen-client` ensures client-go compatibility\n144: \n145: ## Acceptance Criteria\n146: \n147: - [ ] CodeInterpreter CRD can be created via kubectl\n148: - [ ] `make gen-crd` produces valid CRD YAML in `manifests/charts/base/crds/`\n149: - [ ] `make gen-client` succeeds without type errors\n150: - [ ] Go types compile without errors (`go build ./pkg/apis/...`)\n\n(End of file - total 150 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Proposal: AR-002 — CRD CodeInterpreter 类型定义\n\n## Summary\n\nDefine Kubernetes Custom Resource Definition (CRD) types for `CodeInterpreter` in the `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1` module. This type enables the AgentCube control plane to manage code execution environment specifications programmatically.\n\n## Purpose\n\n`CodeInterpreter` CRD provides a declarative way to configure code execution environments for AI agents:\n\n- **Container orchestration**: Define container images, resources, environment variables\n- **Session management**: Configure max session duration, idle timeout\n- **Authentication**: Support for authentication modes (picod, none)\n- **Warm pool**: Pre-warmed pod scaling for faster cold start\n\nThis CRD is consumed by:\n- Workload Manager (creates/updates CodeInterpreter resources)\n- client-go library (generated, provides typed clients, listers, informers)\n- Helm chart CRDs (generated from these types via controller-gen)\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775839967565,"end":1775839967572}}}}
